    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "The implementation for this feature is in https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/master/macros/src/console_fmt.rs, you will see tests at the bottom there too. `%e` for exponential and `%x` for hex formats seems reasonable\r\n\r\nOne thing that would be nice is if you can do `%e` to let forge choose the exponent and `%ne` for any `n`, e.g. `%6e` to specify I want the exponent to be 6, which is useful for formatting token amounts.\r\n\r\n@mattsse any thoughts here? Going to assign to @y1cunhui ",
